ὓ Α Civic Wreath was voted by the senate to Julius Caesar as the saviour of the country, and thenceforward one was kept hung up at the door of the emperor's palace.

‘· A golden crown decorated with turrets was given to the first man who scaled the walls of a besieged city, and one ornamented with a palisade to the first who crossed a palisaded trench; and in particular one variety of triumpha! crown was called corona aurea. One called corona navalis or rostrata, decorated with the ‘beaks ’ of ships, was awarded to the first sailor who boarded an enemy ship, and later to a naval commander who won a signal victory.
